Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(halved, peeled and thinly sliced). Trim the
root and the dark green leafy part from the @leek{1}(trimmed). Halve lengthways then
thinly slice widthways. Trim the @courgette{1}(trimmed) then quarter lengthways.
Chop widthways into small pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove}(peeled and
grated) (or use a garlic press). Pick the tarragon leaves from their stalks and
roughly chop @tarragon{1/2}(leaves picked and roughly chopped, stalks discarded).

Put a large #saucepan{} of water with 0.5 @salt{1/2%tsp} on to boil for the pasta.
Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #frying pan{} on high heat. Add the
@diced chicken breast{260%g} and cook until brown all over, ~{7-8%minutes}. Season
with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Remove from the pan and set aside.

> Tip: Do this in batches if necessary, you want the chicken to brown not stew.

Reduce the heat to medium and add the onion, leek and courgette to your now empty
pan. Cook until they begin to soften, ~{4-5%minutes}. Add the garlic and cook for
~{1%minute} more. Return the chicken to the pan. Pour in the @water{100%ml} and
add the @chicken stock powder{1}. Stir to dissolve, then bring to the boil.

Reduce the heat to low and half cover the pan with a #lid{} (or use some
@?foil{}). Simmer until reduced by half, about ~{10%minutes}.

> Tip: Take the lid off after 5 mins if there is too much liquid in the pan.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, pop the rigatoni in your #pot{} of boiling water. Cook the
@rigatoni pasta{200%g} for ~{12%minutes}. Drain in a #colander{} and return to
the pan off the heat. Drizzle with @oil{drizzle} and stir through to stop it
sticking together.

Stir the @crème fraîche{150%g} through the chicken. Add a squeeze of
@lemon{1/2}(juiced) and the tarragon to taste, together with the drained pasta.
Season to taste with salt and pepper if needed, then serve in #deep bowls{} and
enjoy!